{"type":"Film","id":"FR2018_060","slug":"fr2018-060-le-collier-rouge","title":{"native":"Le Collier rouge","english":"The Red Collar"},"release":{"type":"Unknown","date":"2018-03-28","year":2018},"filmType":"Fiction film","directors":[{"id":"Jean Becker","slug":"jean-becker","name":"Jean Becker","birthYear":1933,"deathYear":0,"gender":"Male identifying","nationality":"France"}],"genre":["Drama","Historical film (Heritage Film)"],"media":{"posterUrl":"https://medias.unifrance.org/medias/129/214/185985/format_page/the-red-collar.jpg","trailerUrl":"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=IoBNNQycV8A"},"synopsis":{"native":"Dans une petite ville, écrasée par la chaleur de l’été, en 1919, un héros de la guerre est retenu prisonnier au fond d’une caserne déserte. Devant la porte, son chien tout cabossé aboie jour et nuit. Non loin de là, dans la campagne, une jeune femme usée par le travail de la terre, trop instruite cependant pour être une simple paysanne, attend et espère. Le juge qui arrive pour démêler cette affaire est un aristocrate dont la guerre a fait vaciller les principes. Trois personnages et, au milieu d’eux, un chien, qui détient la clef du drame…","english":"In 1919, in a small town under the crushing heat of summer, a war hero is held prisoner in an abandoned barracks. Outside, his mangy dog barks night and day. Not far off in the countryside, an extraordinarily intelligent young woman works the land, waiting and hoping. A judge whose principles have been sorely shaken by the war is coming to sort out this case of which it is better not to speak. Three characters. In their midst, a dog that holds the key to their destinies and this intriguing plot."},"production":[{"country":"France","share":"Majority coproducer"},{"country":"Brazil","share":"Minority coproducer"}],"characters":[{"id":"FR2018_060_01","film":"FR2018_060","person":{"id":"François Cluzet","slug":"francois-cluzet","name":"François Cluzet","birthYear":1955,"deathYear":0,"gender":"Male identifying","na